        <p> {{ page.overview.intro|raw }} to just get away. First we had the plan to look for a small cabin somewhere in the mountains. Then there were considerations to go to Egypt, and in the end we found cheap flights to New York. </p>
        <p> Today we flew to New York via Amsterdam. This time we were going across the big pond with KLM. Actually a renowned airline from the Netherlands, where we've only heard good things so far. Unfortunately, the Amsterdam plane was very cramped. It felt even tighter than the low-cost airline Ryanair. We won't mention the dirty toilets, but the good food and friendly staff were great. </p>
        <p> After landing in New York, it took about 1.5 hours until we were through passport control and customs. But we were apparently just in time, because when we finally got through, there were about three times as many people behind us. </p>
        <p> Another hour later we arrived in Manhattan, more specifically at the Hilton Garden Inn between Wall Street and the Staten Island Ferry. Our room is on the 20th floor and has a city view. City view means looking at the next three skyscrapers. </p>

